The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 New Delhi, Jan. 2: The National Aluminium Co has raised the prices of aluminium by Rs 3,500 per tonne. This is the fifth time in the last four months Nalco revised aluminium prices. ?We have raised aluminium price by Rs 3,500 per tonne in view of the rising international price of the metal, especially on the London Stock Exchange,? said Nalco chairman-cum-managing director C.R. Pradhan. The company expects the price to stabilise after January.

 New Delhi, Jan. 2: After two months of successive reductions, Indian Oil Corp today raised jet fuel prices by up to 7.75 per cent. Oil marketing firms like IOC, Bharat Petroleum and Hindustan Petroleum had cut aviation turbine fuel prices in November and December.

 Mumbai, Jan. 2: Tata Consultancy Services (TCS) today said it appointed Neville Roach as chairman of TCS-FNS, the Australian company formed after TCS acquired Sydney-based Financial Network Services in October.

 Calcutta, Jan. 2: Aptech Ltd has received shareholders? approval for raising foreign institutional investors? stake to 74 per cent.

 New Delhi, Jan. 2: The civil aviation ministry is likely to get Rs 3,046.93 crore from the government for the next fiscal, including a gross budgetary support of Rs 130 crore.




